request.description:
Use this endpoint to match hashtag information based on [input values](#a7bea20a-f496-431b-9403-337231c4a22e) and return output fields in the response.

**Input params**

| Parameter | DataType | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| companyId | String | Required. The ID of the company for which you want to find hashtags. |

**Output fields**

| Field | Description |
| --- | --- |
| tag | Hashtag |
| searchString | Hashtag string |
| displayLabel | Hashtag string for display |
| description | Hashtag description |
| group | Hashtag group |
| parentCategory | Hashtag parent category |
| displayScore | Display hashtag score (yes or no) |
| scoreUnit | Hashtag score unit |
| hidden | Show or hide hashtag (Boolean) |
| label | Hashtag label |
| categorizedFlag | Categorized (Boolean) |

request.description: Returns a list of fields you can use as input for the [Hashtags Enrich](#886fb5cc-b587-4f26-bd68-892798d45ffe) endpoint.

response.name: Get Hashtag Enrich Inputs

item.description:
Use [Hashtags Enrich](#886fb5cc-b587-4f26-bd68-892798d45ffe) to retrieve company hashtags using valid query parameters. A Hashtags Enrich request requires you to specify the input parameters about the company you are enriching.

Refer to the examples provided to build a valid JSON request. Use the [Hashtags Enrich Inputs](#a7bea20a-f496-431b-9403-337231c4a22e) endpoint to retrieve a list of valid input parameters you can provide.

item.name: Intent Enrich

body.raw:
{
	"companyName": "ZoomInfo",
	"companyWebsite": "zoominfo.com",
	"companyId": 344589814,
	"topics": ["Cloud Applications", "Cloud Computing", "Cloud Infrastructure", "Corporate Culture", "Credit Card Fraud", "Direct Deposit", "eFulfillment Service", "Google Search", "Healthcare Law", "Hours of Work", "In-App Advertising", "Incentive Compensation", "Java", "Legal", "Mobile / Wireless", "Mobile Apps", "Mobile Security", "Mobile Wallet", "Node.js", "Organizational Culture", "Risk Management Services", "Video Conferencing"],
	"signalStartDate": "2020-04-01",
	"signalEndDate": "2020-05-31",
	"signalScoreMin": 80,
	"signalScoreMax": 100,
	"audienceStrengthMin": "C",
	"audienceStrengthMax": "A",
	"sortBy": "issueDate",
	"sortOrder": "desc"
}

request.description:
Use this endpoint to enrich intent data for a company based on [input values](#2dcbe844-7f1f-45f3-ae32-2598ccec5be4) and return the desired [output fields](#fc4083cf-6179-4f0f-8b9b-80aedc2e3e67) in the response.

Intent data is online behavior-based activity across the internet that links buyers and accounts to a topic. Key terminology includes:

- **Topics and categories** - The Intent Enrich endpoint returns specific intent topics for a company based on your subscription. Multiple topics fall under a single category.
- **Signal** - Recent content consumption activity for a specific topic by people at a company
- **Signal Score** - Indicates a company's interest in a topic based on how recent content consumption compares to a historical baseline.
- **Audience Strength** - Indicates the size of the group at the company conducting research in this topic.
    

This endpoint can support up to 50 Intent topics separated by “OR” condition, and up to 12 Intent topics separated with “AND” condition. The difference between Start and End date should not be more than 90 days.

**Input params**

| Parameter | DataType | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| companyWebsite | String | Company website URL in [http://www.example.com](http://www.example.com) format |
| companyId | String | Unique ZoomInfo identifier for a company |
| companyName | String | Company name |
| topics | String | Intent topics. Separate multiple topics with the pipe symbol. See the **Intent Topics** lookup endpoint for values. |
| signalStartDate | String | Start date for a company signaling interest in a topic |
| signalEndDate | String | End date for a company signaling interest in a topic |
| signalScoreMin | Integer | Minimum signal score. Use with `signalScoreMax` to form a range. Minimum score is 60 and maximum is 100. |
| signalScoreMax | Integer | Maximum signal score. Use with `signalScoreMin` to form a range. Minimum score is 60 and maximum is 100. |
| audienceStrengthMin | String | Minimum audience strength score. Use with `audienceStrengthMax` to form a range. Values are `A`, `B`, `C`, `D`, and `E`, with `A` indicating a larger audience. |
| audienceStrengthMax | String | Maximum audience strength score. Use with `audienceStrengthMin` to form a range. Values are `A`, `B`, `C`, `D`, and `E`, with `A` indicating a larger audience. |
| findRecommendedContacts | Boolean | Choose whether to get the recommended contacts using the findRecommendedContacts flag. Default is `true`. |
| rpp | Integer | Limits the results returned to the given number of results per page. Default is 25. |
| page | Integer | Provides the results for the given page, used in conjunction with `rpp` |
| sortOrder | String | Provide `sortBy` if specifying `sortOrder`. Valid values are `asc`, `ascending`, `desc`, and `descending`. By default, results are sorted in descending order. |
| sortBy | String | Sort results by valid output fields. Valid values are: `signalDate`, `signalScore`, `category`, `topic`, `audienceStrength`. |

**Output fields**

| Field | Description |
| --- | --- |
| id | Unique ZoomInfo identifier for a topic |
| category | Intent category |
| topic | Intent topic |
| signalScore | Signal score for the topic |
| audienceStrength | Audience strength for the topic |
| signalDate | Date the signal was identified |
| companyId | Unique ZoomInfo identifier for a company |
| companyName | Company name |
| companyWebsite | Company website URL in [http://www.example.com](http://www.example.com) format |
| companyHasOtherTopicConsumption | Indicates whether a company has other topics with increased consumption. Values are `true` and `false`. |
| recommendedContacts | Suggested contacts at the company that are related to the intent topic |
| topSignalLocations | Up to 3 top Intent signal locations |

item.name: News Enrich

request.description:
Use this endpoint to match company news information based on [input values](#d58425e5-a4a4-4af0-ad01-fa7bbf91ca84) and return the desired [output fields](#254b86e3-e51b-450d-8704-95e4da168874) in the response.

The News Enrich endpoint returns a list of news articles related to a specified company:

- News Enrich requests require a valid ZoomInfo Company ID as an input parameter
- By default, each request will return the 10 most recent news articles associated with the company record
- You can filter the news articles returned by adjusting the input parameters
    

**Input params**

| Parameter | DataType | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| companyId | String | Unique ZoomInfo identifier for a company |
| limit | Integer | Number of articles to return per page. The maximum limit is 100. |
| page | Integer | Provides the results for the given page. Used in conjunction with `limit`. |
| categories | String | Category of news articles. See the News Categories endpoint for values. |
| url | ArrayList | Search news by text contained in URL strings. You must specify a minimum of 5 characters per input. |
| pageDateMin | String | Specify the earliest publishing date for news articles returned. For example, `2020-01-01` will return all news articles published on or after Jan 1, 2020. |
| pageDateMax | String | Specify the latest publishing date for news articles articles. For example, `2020-01-31` will return all new articles published on or before Jan 31, 2020. |

**Output fields**

| Field | Description |
| --- | --- |
| companyId | Unique ZoomInfo identifier for a company |
| companyName | Company name |
| domain | News article domain |
| title | News article title |
| url | News article URL |
| imageUrl | News article image URL |
| pageDate | News article date |
| categories | News article categories |
| description | News article content description |

request.description:
Use this endpoint to match company scoop information based on [input values](#4ebf5d05-d819-4336-977f-2fe72dc6ac19) and return the desired [output fields](##6c2de74a-e026-401b-8910-503ae7aa57c8) in the response.

The Scoop Enrich endpoint returns a list of scoops related to a specified company:

- Scoop Enrich requests require one of the following: a valid ZoomInfo `companyId`, `companyName`, or `companyWebsite` as an input parameter
- If you do not provide a date range for when the scoop was published, the last 30 days of scoop records matching the request are returned
- For charging purposes, each scoop returned is counted as a record
    

**Input params**

| Parameter | DataType | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| companyId | String | ZoomInfo unique identifier for the company. Will accept a comma-separated list. |
| companyName | String | Company name |
| companyWebsite | String | Company domain |
| publishedStartDate | String | Starting date to search for scoops based on when published. Form a range using publishedEndDate or omit publishedEndDate to search to the current date. Uses YYYY-MM-DD format. |
| publishedEndDate | String | Ending date to search for scoops based on when published. Form a range using publishedEndDate. Uses YYYY-MM-DD format. |
| updatedSinceCreation | Boolean | Include scoops that have been updated since publishedStartDate |
| scoopType | String | Retrieve scoops based on type (e.g., earnings, awards, partnerships and so on). See the **Scoop Types** lookup endpoint for valid inputs. |
| scoopTopic | String | Retrieve scoops based on topic (e.g., integrations, technology, compliance and so on). See the **Scoop Topics** lookup endpoint for valid inputs. |
| department | String | Retrieve scoops based on department (IT, finance, HR and so on). See the **Scoop Departments** lookup endpoint for valid inputs. |
| scoopId | String | ZoomInfo unique identifier for a scoop. Will accept a comma-separated list. |
| description | String | Search for scoops based on description. Will accept a comma-separated list of keywords. |
| rpp | Integer | Limits the results returned to the given number of results per page. Default is 25. |
| page | Integer | Provides the results for the given page, used in conjunction with `rpp` |
| sortOrder | String | Provide `sortBy` if specifying `sortOrder`. Valid values are `asc`, `ascending`, `desc`, and `descending`. By default, results are sorted in descending order. |
| sortBy | String | Sort results by valid output fields: `scoopId`, `originalPublishedDate`, `description`, `link`, or `linkText` |

**Output fields**

| Field | Description |
| --- | --- |
| id | ZoomInfo unique identifier for a scoop |
| publishedDate | Publish date for a scoop. If updated, this date will reflect that last updated date. |
| originalPublishedDate | Initial publish date for a scoop |
| linkText | Link text for a scoop |
| link | URL for the scoop |
| description | Short description for the scoop contents |
| topics | Topic(s) associated with a scoop |
| updateText | Text related to an updated scoop |
| types | Type(s) associated with a scoop |
| companyId | ZoomInfo unique identifier for a company |
| companyName | Company name |
| contacts | Contacts associated with a scoop |

request.description:
Use this endpoint to create a webhook.

**About enabling a webhook**

When creating a webhook, we recommend initially setting the `enabled` parameter to `false` so that you can ensure that:

- Your target URL is accessible using the [Validate Target URL](#5fabb9e4-aff2-4651-8404-8b061675eda0) endpoint.
- You've established a validation method in your app for the webhook verification token that will be generated with this request.
    

Once you've completed these tasks, you can activate the webhook using the [Update Webhook](#c853f6cd-10e7-4103-9896-19827c4c5a8a) endpoint, updating the webhook's `enabled` status to `true`.

**Input params**

| Parameter | DataType | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| title | String | Title for the webhook |
| enabled | Boolean | Determines whether the webhook is initially enabled or disabled. |
| targetUrl | String | Destination URL for the webhook data. Must be in `https://` format. |
| subscriptions | ArrayList | Specify the `eventType` and `objectType` for the webhook. Also specify the `fullPayload` value (`true` for full payload, `false` for only changed attributes.)|

**Output fields**

| Field | Description |
| --- | --- |
| id | Unique ZoomInfo identifier for the webhook |
| title | Title for the webhook |
| enabled | Displays whether the webhook is enabled or disabled |
| targetUrl | Destination URL for the webhook data |
| createdDate | Timestamp for when the webhook was created |
| verificationToken | Verification token generated when the webhook was created |
| subscriptions | List of subscriptions. Each subscription includes the `createdDate`, `modifiedDate`, `eventType`, `objectType` and a unique `subscriptionId`. |

request.description:
Use this endpoint to update an existing webhook, including its enabled status, target URL, and subscription details.

Specify the webhook by appending the webhook `id` in the request URL. For example:

`https://api.zoominfo.com/webhooks/213786430`

When using the Update Webhook endpoint, values you provide in the JSON body of your request overwrite values in the existing webhook. Common scenarios for using this endpoint include the following.

**Enable a webhook**

As described in the [Create Webhook](#6cbb2c08-cb50-4b15-9a01-a2d0d3dabaa1) endpoint, we recommend initially configuring a new webhook as disabled so you can ensure the target URL is reachable, and the verification token is in place in your integrated app. Once these tasks are complete, you can use the Update Webhook endpoint to enable the webhook.

For example, send a request specifying the webhook `id` in the URL to change the `enabled` value to `true`:

Request URL:

`https://api.zoominfo.com/webhooks/{webhook_id}`

JSON body:

```
{
    "enabled": true
}

```

**Update webhook subscription details**

Example: Your webhook has a subscription with the `objectType` set to `Company`, you can change it to `Contact` using the Update Webhook endpoint.

Request URL:

`https://api.zoominfo.com/webhooks/{webhook_id}`

JSON body:

```
{
    "subscriptions": [
        {
            "subscriptionId": "393093719",
            "eventType": "Update",
            "objectType": "Contact"
        }
    ]
} 

```

**Add a new objectType to a subscription**

Example: Your webhook has a subscription that includes only the `Contact` `objectType`. You can add the `Company` `objectType` to the subscription.

Request URL:

`https://api.zoominfo.com/webhooks/{webhook_id}`

JSON body:

```
{
    "subscriptions": [
        {
            "eventType": "Update",
            "objectType": "Company"
        }
    ]
} 

```

**Delete a subscription**

You can delete a subscription by simply sending the `subscriptionId` in your request without specifying any subscription parameters.

Request URL:

`https://api.zoominfo.com/webhooks/{webhook_id}`

JSON body:

```
{
    "subscriptions": [
        {
            "subscriptionId": "836880237"
        }
    ]
}

```

**Input params**

| Parameter | DataType | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| title | String | Title for the webhook |
| enabled | Boolean | Enable or disable the webhook |
| targetUrl | String | Destination URL for the webhook data. Must be in `https://` format. |
| subscriptions | ArrayList | Specify the `eventType` and `objectType` for the webhook |

**Output fields**

| Field | Description |
| --- | --- |
| id | Unique ZoomInfo identifier for the webhook |
| title | Title for the webhook |
| enabled | Displays whether the webhook is enabled or disabled |
| targetUrl | Destination URL for the webhook data |
| createdDate | Timestamp for when the webhook was created |
| verificationToken | Verification token generated when the webhook was created |
| subscriptions | List of subscriptions. Each subscription includes the `createdDate`, `modifiedDate`, `eventType`, `objectType` and a unique `subscriptionId`. |

item.description:
Use the Bulk APIs to search, retrieve, and enrich large ZoomInfo company and contact datasets through asynchronous batch processes.

With 20x more records than Contact and Company Search and 400x more records than the Contact and Company Enrich, you can leverage Bulk APIs for data ingestion and enrichment at scale.

**Bulk Search API**

With the Bulk Search API you can:

*   Search for up to 200K records with a single search query
*   Preview or redeem up to 500 records per page
    

Two job types are available with the Bulk Search APIs:

*   The Preview job type returns a company or contact search results preview to help identify records best suited for enrichment. Credits are not charged for the Preview job type.
*   The Redeem job type enables data retrieval for ingestion, returning selected output fields for a given contact or company. A credit is charged for each unique record that is redeemed.
    

When you submit a search request, an asynchronous job is started, and a job_id is instantly returned. You can use the job_id to check the status of the job and retrieve results.

**Bulk Enrich API**

With the Bulk Enrich API you can:

*   Enrich up to 10K records in a single job
*   Retrieve up to 500 results per page
    

When you submit an enrich request, an asynchronous job is started, and a job_id is instantly returned. You can use the job_id to check the status of the job and enrich results.

**Rate Limiting**

*   You can have up to 5 "active" jobs (Jobs that are in progress are active jobs. Once a job is completed, you can proceed to creating another job)
*   You can create up to 1 job per second
*   Each job you create expires after 24 hours
Use the Bulk APIs and Monitoring API to discover and enrich millions of records, at scale, and have the freshest data available at all times, automatically.
The ZoomInfo Enterprise API is comprised of Standard APIs and Scaling APIs.

item.description:
The Websights API identifies anonymous website traffic by resolving IP addresses (IPv4 & IPv6) to return company and ISP profiles and IP geolocation details.

**Company vs. ISP response data**

If the IP address belongs to a company, details about the company are returned including geolocation details. For example:

```
"data": {
    "company": {
        "city": "Vancouver",
        "country": "United States",
        "employeeCount": 1300,
        "id": 344589814,
        "industries": [
            "media.data",
            "media",
            "software"
        ],
        "name": "Zoom Information, Inc.",
        "revenue": 400000,
        "state": "Washington",
        "street": "805 Broadway St Suite 900",
        "ticker": "",
        "website": "www.zoominfo.com",
       "zipCode": "98660"
    },
    "geoLocation": {
        "location_long": -122.672,
        "location_lat": 45.627,
        "country_code": "US",
        "province": "Washington"
    }

```

If the IP address belongs to an internet service provider (ISP), details about the ISP are returned including geolocation details. For example:

```
    "data": {
        "geoLocation": {
            "location_long": -71.06616,
            "location_lat": 42.45843,
            "country_code": "US",
            "province": "Massachusetts"
        },
        "ispInfo": {
            "domain": "comcast.com",
            "ip_hi_string": "73.143.255.255",
            "ip_lo_string": "73.142.0.0",
            "name": "Comcast Cable Communications, Inc.",
            "type": "isp"
        }

```

**Charging mechanism**

Your account is provisioned with an allocated number of records that you can retrieve over a 1-year period. A record is either a company for which ZoomInfo has data, or an Internet Service Provider (ISP). If a query does not match a company or ISP, no record is charged.

item.name: Release Notes
item.description:
ZoomInfo Enterprise APIs are updated frequently with new features and improvements. Refer to these release notes to track ongoing updates.

## September 18, 2023

If your organization has access to the WebSights API, we've added a new output field called `confidenceScore` to the data that can be returned for a company.

- Confidence Score indicates the certainty of an IP matching a domain.
- The score ranges from 0.00 to 1.00.
- Only matches with a score of 0.3 or above are shown by default.  
    Contact your Account Manager for lower-scoring matches. It could be empty.
    

## August 15, 2023

When using the Contact Search API, you can specify that direct phone (`directPhone`) in `requiredFields` to only return contacts that have the direct phone numbers. Use the `requiredFields` input parameter to specify a list of required fields for each record returned. This can include: `email`, `phone` (direct or company), `directPhone`, `mobilePhone`, `personalEmail`. You can include a comma-separated list of these fields.

## June 19, 2023

### Monitoring API Update: Support for `changedAttributes`

We have updated the Monitoring API to support `changedAttributes`. This feature indicates what information has been changed in a webhook payload for Contact and Company. For example, it can specify details such as "email and Job title changed for Joe Smith".

## March 16, 2023

### Bulk APIs `sortBy` Feature Issue Resolved

We have fixed an issue that was causing the `sortBy` feature in Bulk Contact Search APIs to fail. Users can now sort data without experiencing any issues.

## March 14, 2023

### Documentation Update: New API Bundles

We have updated our documentation to reflect new bundle organization. The bundles have been restructured as follows:

- The Bulk APIs and Webhooks/Monitoring API are now exclusively part of Scaling APIs.
- The Standard APIs remain as they are - realtime Search and Enrich APIs.
    

## February 14, 2023

### Updates to Alexa Rank and Introduction of Domain Rank in Company Enrich APIs

We've made some changes to our Company Enrich APIs regarding website popularity metrics:

- The `alexaRank` field is now deprecated. Previously, this field provided a measure of website popularity, ranking millions of websites in order of popularity based on data from Alexa.
- We've introduced a new field, `domainRank`, powered by SimilarWeb. Domain Rank is calculated based on an algorithm determining a site's monthly web traffic. The lower the `domainRank` number, the higher the site's rank. This will provide more accurate and comprehensive data about a website's performance. Please use `domainRank` for your future needs.
    

## February 1, 2023

### Performance Improvements to Bulk APIs

We've made a number of performance improvements to our Bulk APIs. These enhancements aim to provide faster responses and improved efficiency when handling large data sets.

## January 19, 2023

### New Feature

**Location Enrich API**

Location Enrich now supports two new output fields.

`"locationEmployeeCount" : 2342` This indicates the number of employees at a physical location of a company.

`"locationName" : Wholefoods Boston` This indicates the name of the company at this physical location, this can include names of subsidiaries/child/acquired companies

## December 5, 2022

### New Feature

**Contact Search API**

You can now sort contact search results by their Accuracy Score (`"sortBy": "contactAccuracyScore"`). Default is descending.

### Improvement

**Contact Search API**

When searching for contacts using phone numbers, even if there are special characters, we will still be able to process them. (eg., "(999) - 999 -9999") will be processed. Alphabets are not allowed (eg., (999)- 999 - 999W))

### Bug Fixes

**Resolved an issue with locationSearchType in Contact Search API**

An issue that gave bad responses when passed in PersonANDHQ is now resolved.

## November 22, 2022

### Improvements

**WebSights API and IP lookup via Company Enrich API**

In order to provide better quality matching, we've made improvements to our matching logic to filter out matches that fall below our quality Confidence Score. You will see better company matches and more ISP matches when there is no company match., but rest assured we are confident in them!

## September 21, 2022

### Improvements

**Enterprise API**

Added `yearsOfExperience` as an output for Contact Enrich.

Fixed an issue where UK postal codes were not supported.

Made performance improvement across all APIs.

**Bulk Enrich API**

Added `yearsOfExperience` as an output for Bulk Contact Enrich.

### Bug Fixes

Fixed an issue where UK postal codes were not supported.

## September 15, 2022

### Enhancement

**Enterprise API**

Made performance improvements across all APIs.

## August 23, 2022

### New Feature

**Contact Search API**

In Contact Search API, you can search for contacts based on their `yearsOfExperience`.

## July 6, 2022

### New Feature

**Contact Search API & Contact Enrich API**

In Contact Search API, you can search for contacts based on their `techSkills`.

In Contact Enrich API, you can export `techSkills` as part of your response.

## June 3, 2022

### Improvements

**Company Master API**

An issue with certain URLs returning timeout error is now resolved.

## June 2, 2022

## New Feature

**Company Master API**

The Company Master API now supports company "HQ" ID as an input (`zi_c_company_id`).

In addition, the Company Master API now supports two new output fields:

1. `zi_c_domestic_parent_location_id` - Retrieves the domestic parent's location ID
2. `zi_c_is_immediate_parent` - Checks if that location is the immediate parent as well
    

### Improvements

**Fixed an issue with businessModel and employeeCountByDepartment in Company Enrich**

An issue with the `businessModel` and `employeeCountByDepartment` outputs in the Company Enrich API is now resolved.

## May 26, 2022

## New Feature

**Intent Enrich API**

Intent Enrich now supports Intent signal location (`topSignalLocations`) as part of the output response.

### Improvements

**Fixed an issue with requiredFields**

An issue with the requiredFields in Contact Search API and Bulk Contact Search API is now resolved.

## May 18, 2022

## New Feature

**Bulk Enrich API**

With the new Bulk Enrich API, you can enrich 400x more records than the current Contact Enrich and Company Enrich endpoints. With Bulk Enrich you can:

- Enrich up to 10K records in a single Enrich job
- Retrieve up to 500 results per page
    

See the [Bulk API](https://) for details on how to use the new [Bulk Contact Enrich](https://) and [Bulk Company Enrich](https://) endpoints.

### Improvements

**Boolean operators for Company Name in Contact Search**

You can now use OR and NOT operators to include or exclude companies by name when using the `companyName` input in Contact Search.

**Improved matching logic for Company Master API**

Company Master API now has improved matching logic.

## April 27, 2022

### New Feature

**Hide European Union (EU) contact information**

You can now hide contact information from being returned for contacts belonging to the EU region by enabling the **HideEU** toggle in the Admin Portal.

By enabling the toggle, you will still receive the contacts in the response, but certain information for that profile will not be returned via the API.

### Improvements

**Industry fields with code in Company Enrich API outputs**

We have added 3 new fields in the Company Enrich output fields to return industries along with its code for better understanding.

1. `primaryIndustryCode`
2. `primarySubIndustryCode`
3. `industryCodes`
    

**Industry fields with code in Contact Enrich API outputs**

We have added 3 new fields in the Contact Enrich output fields to return industries along with its code for better understanding.

1. `companyPrimaryIndustryCode`
2. `companyPrimarySubIndustryCode`
3. `companyIndustryCodes`
    

## April 18, 2022

### Improvements

**Bulk Search API Results per page**

Due to performance reasons, the default results per page will be 500 records per page. We do support an RPP of up to 1000 per page, however, depending on the amount of data, we recommend opting in for the default to allow for a seamless experience.

**Scoops Search and Enrich API**

We have made performance improvements in the Scoops Search and Enrich APIs.

## April 7, 2022

### Improvements

**Updated field names**

The following field names have been updated, with all "Global" fields renamed as "Ultimate". For backward compatibility, we will continue to support both the old field names and the new field names for the foreseeable future.

| Old field name | New field name |
| --- | --- |
| ZI_C_IS_GLOBAL_PARENT | ZI_C_IS_ULTIMATE_PARENT |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_COMPANY_ID | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_COMPANY_ID |
| ZI_ES_GLOBAL_PARENT_ECID | ZI_ES_ULTIMATE_PARENT_ECID |
| ZI_ES_GLOBAL_PARENT_LOCATION_ID | ZI_ES_ULTIMATE_PARENT_LOCATION_ID |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_NAME | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_NAME |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_URL | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_URL |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_STREET | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_STREET |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_STREET_2 | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_STREET_2 |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_CITY | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_CITY |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_ZIP | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_ZIP |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_STATE | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_STATE |
| ZI_C_GLOBAL_PARENT_COUNTRY | ZI_C_ULTIMATE_PARENT_COUNTRY |

## March 22, 2022

### Improvements

**Improved primary industry logic**

We’ve improved the logic for the 'primaryIndustriesOnly' field. With this update, the `industryCodes` will only match the primary industry if the `primaryIndustriesOnly` input is set to true.

**Improved charging logic for IP Enrich**

When using IP Enrich, a request must return a company profile in order to expend a credit. Requests that return only ISP and/or location data will not expend a credit.

## March 16, 2022

### New Features

**Department Employee Count as an output field in Company Enrich**

We’ve added `employeeCountByDepartment` as an output for Company Enrich that shows the department employee count for a company.

### Improvements

**Intent Enrich improvement**

The Intent Enrich endpoint can support up to 50 topics separated by “OR” condition, and up to 12 topics separated with “AND” condition. The difference between Start and End date should not be more than 90 days.

## March 14, 2022

### New Features

**Buying Committee filter for Contact Search**

We’ve added `filterByBuyingCommittee` as an input for Contact Search. This Boolean flag will filter results based on Buying Committees set up for the account by their organization’s individual users using the platform UI.

## February 17, 2022

## New Features

**Bulk API**

We've added four new endpoints that provide bulk search and redeem capabilities for Contacts and Companies. The [Bulk API](https://) enables Enterprise API customers to search and retrieve large ZoomInfo Company and Contact datasets at scale through asynchronous batch processes.

## February 4, 2022

### New Features

**Company department budget support**  
For Company Search API: You can now filter for companies using department budget fields:

- marketingDepartmentBudgetMin
- marketingDepartmentBudgetMax
- financeDepartmentBudgetMin
- financeDepartmentBudgetMax
- itDepartmentBudgetMin
- itDepartmentBudgetMax
- hrDepartmentBudgetMin
- hrDepartmentBudgetMax
    

Department budget amount in thousands (e.g., 1 = 1000, 500 = 500,000). Minimum value is 0, maximum value is 2147483647 (approximately 2 trillion).

**Web reference keyword support**  
For Contact Search API: You can now search for contacts using Web Reference Keywords (`webReferences`). Use this to search for a contact by their web reference keywords. The default criteria is OR between multiple values and should only contain English letters and numbers.

**Intent Search and Intent Enrich API updates**  
When using Intent Search or Intent Enrich, you can now choose whether to get the recommended contacts using the `findRecommendedContacts` flag. You should expect a performance impact (higher latency) when when this flag is set to `true`, which is the default.

## January 11, 2022

### New Feature

For Company Search API: You can now search for company using `businessModel` (B2C, B2B, B2G). Default is All.

For Company Enrich API: You can now specify `businessModel` in the company enrich output field.

### Bug Fixes

Scoops enrich now correctly returns Scoops with the company name and contact name (if available) in the Scoops description.

## December 2, 2021

### Improvements

For Contact Search, we added the ability to search for contacts using `supplementalEmail`.

For Company Master API, we improved the matching logic of Name only inputs. Name only inputs will return the HQ location by default unless location specific details are provided in the inputs.

## November 22, 2021

### Improvements

Added `departmentBudgets` as an output to the Company Enrich endpoint. Returns estimated budget values including `marketingBudget`, `financeBudget`, `itBudget` and `hrBudget`.

## November 17, 2021

### Improvements

We have added the following new fields as outputs for the Company Master Data Enrich API:

- zi_c_parent_child_confidence_score
- zi_c_is_fortune_100
- zi_c_is_fortune_500
- zi_c_is_s_and_p_500
    

In addition, the following field names are changed for the Company Master Data Enrich API:

| Old field name | New field name |
| --- | --- |
| zi_c_hq_id | zi_c_company_id |
| zi_c_hq_name | zi_c_company_name |
| zi_c_hq_url | zi_c_company_url |
| zi_c_hq_street | zi_c_company_street |
| zi_c_hq_street_2 | zi_c_company_street_2 |
| zi_c_hq_city | zi_c_company_city |
| zi_c_hq_state | zi_c_company_state |
| zi_c_hq_zip | zi_c_company_zip |
| zi_c_hq_country | zi_c_company_country |
| zi_c_hq_cbsa_name | zi_c_company_cbsa_name |
| zi_c_hq_county | zi_c_company_county |
| zi_c_hq_latitude | zi_c_company_latitude |
| zi_c_hq_longitude | zi_c_company_longitude |
| zi_c_hq_verified_address | zi_c_company_verified_address |
| zi_c_hq_employee_range | zi_c_company_employee_range |
| zi_c_hq_employees | zi_c_company_employees |
| zi_c_hq_revenue_range | zi_c_company_revenue_range |
| zi_c_hq_revenue | zi_c_company_revenue |
| zi_c_hq_phone | zi_c_company_phone |
| zi_c_hq_fax | zi_c_company_fax |
| zi_c_immediate_parent_id | zi_c_immediate_parent_company_id |
| zi_c_domestic_parent_id | zi_c_domestic_parent_company_id |
| zi_c_global_parent_id | zi_c_global_parent_company_id |
| zi_c_franchisor_id | zi_c_franchisor_company_id |

## November 3, 2021

### Improvement

We have improved the `logo` field in the Company Enrich endpoint. You will now be able to retrieve the recently updated logos for companies.

## October 13, 2021

### Improvement

A new output field called `matchStatus` is included for the following:

- [Company Enrich](https://)
- [Contact Enrich](https://)
- [Corporate Hierarchy Enrich](https://)
- [Compliance API](https://)
    

The `matchStatus` field is returned in each response to indicate the specific reason that a contact or company was matched, not matched, or not returned.

At the end of each response, the `matchStatus` is output as follows:

```
 "matchStatus": "FULL_MATCH"

 ```

For contacts (Contact Enrich, Corporate Hierarchy Enrich, Compliance API), `matchStatus`can be as follows (in priority order):

- "NO_MATCH"
- "OPT_OUT"
- “FULL_MATCH”
- "COMPANY_ONLY_MATCH"
- "NON_MATCH_BY_REQUIRED_FIELDS"
- "NON_MATCH_BY_LAST_UPDATED_DATE"
- "NON_MATCH_BY_VALID_DATE"
- "NON_MATCH_BY_CONTACT_ACCURACY_MIN"
- "CONTACT_ONLY_MATCH"
- "INVALID_INPUT"
- “LIMIT_EXCEEDED”
- "SERVICE_ERROR"
    

For companies (Company Enrich), `matchStatus` can be as follows (in priority order):

- "NO_MATCH"
- "FULL_MATCH"
- "INVALID_INPUT"
- “LIMIT_EXCEEDED”
- "SERVICE_ERROR"
    

## October 4, 2021

### New Feature

We've added a new API called [Company Master Data Enrich API](https://) that combines ZoomInfo and EverString company data to provide 165M+ company locations with 104M+ company HQs.

## September 8, 2021

### NEW FEATURE

The Contact Enrich endpoint now includes `contactAccuracyScoreMin` in the input fields. This new field will allow users to specify a minimum accuracy score as a criteria to enrich the contact.

### IMPROVEMENTS

We have made improvements in the Scoops Enrich and Intent Enrich endpoints that will reduce the response time.

## August 18, 2021

### New Features

- The `companyFunding` field in Company Enrich output now returns investors along with the funding data (date, type, and amount).
- Webhooks will now trigger a request when there is a change in the `positionStartDate` for a contact.
    

## July 26, 2021

### New Features

- When using Contact Search, you can now specify a range for the start date and end date of a person’s current employment. Use the `positionStartDateMin` and `positionStartDateMax` inputs in Contact Search.
- When using Contact Enrich, you can now include the date on which the contact began their current employment as an output. Specify `positionStartDate` as an output in Contact Enrich.
    

## July 12, 2021

### New Feature

The Contact Enrich endpoint now includes `requiredFields`. This new field will allow users to specify a list of required fields for each record returned. This supports all output fields and can be used as a comma-separated list.

### Improvements

The Webhooks payload now includes only two outputs for `noticeProvidedDate`: either a valid date, or empty. Prior to this update, “Notice Not Required” was included as a valid output.

## June 17, 2021

### Improvements

An issue that caused the usage counts to not reset is now fixed. You will now see your true usage counts when you use the Usage Endpoint.

## June 9, 2021

### Bug Fixes

SicCodes will no longer return a "null" value in the array. There could be a valid SicCode in the array or an empty array if there are no SicCodes associated with it.

## May 24, 2021

### Improvements

LocationSearchType in contact and company search supports the following parameters: `PersonOrHQ`, `PersonAndHQ`, `Person`, `HQ`, `PersonThenHQ`.

## April 28, 2021

### Improvements

`primaryIndustry` field sorting order is now improved. The first value in the `primaryIndustry` is the Primary Industry (example: Media & Internet), and the second value will be the Primary Sub-Industry (example: Social Networks)

## April 22, 2021

### Improvements

- Added `isDefunct` as an output to the Company Enrich endpoint. This value indicates whether a company exists.
    

## March 24, 2021

### New Features

Company Enrich now supports `foundedYear` as an output field.

## March 10, 2021

### Bug Fixes

An issue that caused users to be logged out of the platform session when they authenticated via the API is resolved. (ZOO-19331)

## February 22, 2021

### New Features

Webhooks API: The new Webhooks API provides a set endpoints for creating and managing webhooks you can use to automate managing records in your integrated apps.

### Improvements

For Intent Search and Intent Enrich, we've made the following changes:

- Inputs - Sorting by `trend` is no longer supported
- We are no longer returning `trend` and `newSignal`
    

### Bug Fixes

An issue with the Intent search field which caused some of the requests to fail is now resolved. (ZOO-23050)
